How would you describe Node to a non-technical friend? Node is an engine that runs on Google Chrome. Another 
way of seeing this is like a car and a tune. You can have a racecar. But once you put a tune on the car it 
makes it a lot quicker. 
What does it mean that Node is a JavaScript runtime? JS runtime means your code has been executed. 
What is Node used for? Node lets us run JS on the server. 
